Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the #lid{} and cook for ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the #pot{} from the heat. Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim and thinly slice the @radish{125%g}. Pop the radish into a #small bowl{} with half the @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @salt{¼%tsp}. Mix together and set aside, continuing to stir frequently.

Place a #pan{} over medium heat (without oil). Once hot, dry-fry the @sesame seeds{1%sachet}, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once toasted, remove from the #pan{} and set aside.

> TIP: Watch the seeds closely—they can burn easily.

Trim the @pak choi{1} and halve lengthways. Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Once hot, add the pak choi (cut-side down) and @sugar snap peas{75%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn the pak choi and add a splash of @water{to taste}. Cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{} and cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Wipe and return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Season the @21 Day Aged Irish Sirloin Steak{250%g} with salt and pepper. Once the pan is hot, fry the sirloin until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for medium-rare. Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it more well-done. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned. Once cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{}, cover and allow to rest.

Remove the pan from the heat. Add the @hoisin sauce{2%sachets}, remaining @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet} and a knob of @butter{to taste}. Allow the sauce to warm through, adding a splash of @water{to taste} if you feel it needs loosening. Thinly slice the steak.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between plates. Serve the sugar snap peas, pak choi and pickled radish alongside. Arrange the sliced steak on the rice and drizzle the buttery hoisin sauce over the top. Finish with a scattering of toasted sesame seeds.